    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Kyle Tucker** leading the charge; at a score of 77.55, he is our clear engine against Paddack. The favorable matchup against a 4.64 xERA arm, combined with his elite xwOBA of 0.372 and prime protection in the #4 hole, makes him a lock for production. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** is our next most reliable asset (68.69), benefiting from a surprising +7% boost due to dynamic platoon splits against Suarez, ensuring his presence in the UTIL slot. Meanwhile, **Andy Pages** (63.03) provides excellent value in the outfield, as his matchup against Paddack offers a strong SP skill advantage that pushes him well into our recommended start territory.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Marcell Ozuna**, who landed at a 58.91 score\u2014effectively dead-even with **Nolan Schanuel** and **Miguel Vargas**. Ultimately, **Marcell Ozuna** was benched because his efficiency profile didn't offer the same order-driven floor as our active 1B/3B options. While **Nolan Schanuel** faces a soft 5.57 xERA matchup against Kay and **Miguel Vargas** remains anchored in the #3 spot, we prioritized their positional versatility over the raw power profile of **Marcell Ozuna**. Caution is advised regarding **Liam Hicks** (41.95), whose score is suppressed by a difficult encounter with Yamamoto; while he clears the 40-point threshold for a start, he remains the most volatile element in today's lineup. We will monitor for any late-breaking lineup changes to ensure our stolen base potential remains optimized, especially given the scarcity of speed in today's environment.",
